<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-1323] MultiReader should make a private copy of the subReaders array</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1323</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;Spinoff from here:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;http://mail-archives.apache.org/mod_mbox/lucene-java-user/200806.mbox/%3C88F3F6A4-FBFB-43DF-890D-DB5F0D9A2461@gmail.com%3E&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot;&gt;http://mail-archives.apache.org/mod_mbox/lucene-java-user/200806.mbox/%3C88F3F6A4-FBFB-43DF-890D-DB5F0D9A2461@gmail.com%3E&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Because MultiReader just holds a reference to the array that was passed in, it&apos;s possible to hit scary exceptions (that look like index corruption) if that array is later altered eg by reopening some of the readers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The fix is trivial: just make a private copy.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
